Authorities suspect an arsonist set a fire at the Garold Wayne Interactive Zoological Park in Oklahoma on March 26 that killed seven alligators and a crocodile . 
  One of the alligators reportedly belonged to Michael Jackson . 
  The fire destroyed two reptile enclosures and a video production studio . 
  The founder of the zoo said the fire was set to 'shut him up' One alligator escaped the fire . 
 